+The documents must not survive the drop. Backends differ on what raw post-drop reads do (memory backends lazy-create on access; SQLite-style backends throw on a missing table), so the cross-backend invariant we observe is "the documents do not survive". Re-creating via `ensureBook` is the canonical post-drop access path.
